00:48:04.570 --> 00:48:08.590
we unwittingly fell into--
the problem of the look that

00:48:08.590 --> 00:48:12.100
had become the norm at the deli
started to get not reproduced

00:48:12.100 --> 00:48:15.310
in the other businesses, which
led to a lot of frustration

00:48:15.310 --> 00:48:19.420
and then realizing, from working
with Maggie at ZingTrain a lot

00:48:19.420 --> 00:48:21.010
over the years,
she's taught me when

00:48:21.010 --> 00:48:23.470
you have a big
frustration with somebody,

00:48:23.470 --> 00:48:27.160
it's almost always because you
have an unspoken expectation.

00:48:27.160 --> 00:48:29.710
And then the challenge is to
look inwards and figure out

00:48:29.710 --> 00:48:31.575
what that unspoken
expectation is.

00:48:31.575 --> 00:48:32.950
And then it was
like, well, yeah,

00:48:32.950 --> 00:48:36.070
this is the way
Zingerman's needs to look

00:48:36.070 --> 00:48:39.190
and then being able to then
teach that more actively

00:48:39.190 --> 00:48:41.432
and train people
in how to do it.

00:48:41.432 --> 00:48:43.390
And then, within the
context of the hope stuff,

00:48:43.390 --> 00:48:46.540
is use one look for
the whole organization

00:48:46.540 --> 00:48:50.230
but then allow each business
to have its own manifestation

00:48:50.230 --> 00:48:52.270
of that within the
overall look so that you

00:48:52.270 --> 00:48:54.130
can honor the individuality
of the business

00:48:54.130 --> 00:48:58.427
but not lose the coherence
of the organization overall.

