AUDIENCE: A lot of pressure.

00:49:29.631 --> 00:49:31.630
So when you were talking
about the belief thing,

00:49:31.630 --> 00:49:33.520
I was just curious,
from your point of view,

00:49:33.520 --> 00:49:35.410
I feel like it's very common for
all of us, as you were saying,

00:49:35.410 --> 00:49:36.640
to fall into the circle.

00:49:36.640 --> 00:49:41.020
How do you go about identifying
when you fall into that rut,

00:49:41.020 --> 00:49:43.282
whether it's you or
someone close to you?

00:49:43.282 --> 00:49:44.740
And then a quick
follow-up to that,

00:49:44.740 --> 00:49:49.732
how do you mitigate that to
change the path of the circle?

00:49:49.732 --> 00:49:51.940
ARI WEINZWEIG: Well, there's
a recipe in the new book

00:49:51.940 --> 00:49:53.170
for how to change a belief.

00:49:53.170 --> 00:49:56.150
Because it's easier
said than done.

00:49:56.150 --> 00:49:58.720
If you've had a belief
since you were six,

00:49:58.720 --> 00:50:03.140
the roots are very deep, and
they don't change easily.

00:50:03.140 --> 00:50:05.960
And this is why you can see it
in society all over the world.

00:50:05.960 --> 00:50:08.110
I mean, people will
hold to their belief

00:50:08.110 --> 00:50:11.200
even though the evidence
clearly shows it's wrong.

00:50:11.200 --> 00:50:13.690
But they'll hold to their
beliefs anyways, right?

00:50:13.690 --> 00:50:17.920
So when-- was it
Copernicus or Galileo?--

00:50:17.920 --> 00:50:22.540
when he said that the sun didn't
revolve around the earth--

00:50:22.540 --> 00:50:25.180
which, now, we go, oh,
well, of course the earth

00:50:25.180 --> 00:50:26.200
revolves around the sun.

00:50:26.200 --> 00:50:28.750
But they used to believe the
sun revolved around the earth.

00:50:28.750 --> 00:50:31.670
So when he wrote that in his
book, the Catholic church said,

00:50:31.670 --> 00:50:32.830
well, you can't write that.

00:50:32.830 --> 00:50:33.492
It's wrong.

00:50:33.492 --> 00:50:35.200
In the Bible, it says
it's the other way.

00:50:35.200 --> 00:50:36.991
And he said, yeah, but
this is what's true.

00:50:36.991 --> 00:50:38.350
They said, we don't care.

00:50:38.350 --> 00:50:41.510
You have to take it out.

00:50:41.510 --> 00:50:44.200
So when people have held
a belief for a long time,

00:50:44.200 --> 00:50:46.890
generally, they will work
really hard to maintain

00:50:46.890 --> 00:50:50.440
the belief in the face
of all sorts of evidence.

00:50:50.440 --> 00:50:54.970
I think, for me,
it just made me get

00:50:54.970 --> 00:50:57.875
myself to almost automatically
go, what do I believe?

00:50:57.875 --> 00:51:00.250
And then, I'm like, oh, yeah,
I believe they can't do it.

00:51:00.250 --> 00:51:04.690
Well, if I believe they
can't do it, they're doomed.

00:51:04.690 --> 00:51:07.790
Because if I'm their manager,
they're not going to succeed.

00:51:07.790 --> 00:51:11.200
So then I need to
re-examine my own belief.

00:51:11.200 --> 00:51:12.710
In terms of other people--

00:51:12.710 --> 00:51:15.660
here's the thing-- is you can't
make anybody change a belief.

00:51:19.160 --> 00:51:20.470
It's a internal process.

00:51:20.470 --> 00:51:23.260
And part of what tends
to happen socially

00:51:23.260 --> 00:51:25.884
is people argue with others
that they should change

00:51:25.884 --> 00:51:27.550
their belief, which
I would suggest just

00:51:27.550 --> 00:51:29.770
makes the roots go deeper.

00:51:29.770 --> 00:51:32.270
Even if they're wrong, it just
makes the roots go deeper.

00:51:32.270 --> 00:51:33.620
And this is why people--

00:51:33.620 --> 00:51:36.550
I mean, this is the national
political scene right now.

00:51:36.550 --> 00:51:38.260
No one's going to
change their mind.

00:51:38.260 --> 00:51:40.301
The roots are just going
to go deeper and deeper.

00:51:40.301 --> 00:51:41.350
And I know where I stand.

00:51:41.350 --> 00:51:43.570
But it's not going to convince
anybody else to change

00:51:43.570 --> 00:51:45.280
their mind that
doesn't agree with me.

00:51:45.280 --> 00:51:48.190
So I think, in the end
of the day, all we can do

00:51:48.190 --> 00:51:51.010
is model and share information
and hope for the best.

00:51:51.010 --> 00:51:54.720
Because you can't force anybody.

00:51:54.720 --> 00:51:57.370
I have the most
impact on my own self.

00:51:57.370 --> 00:51:59.510
And that's really where
I can make a difference.

00:51:59.510 --> 00:52:01.750
And if I change my
beliefs for the better,

00:52:01.750 --> 00:52:03.340
then it might change
two other people,

00:52:03.340 --> 00:52:04.910
and it might change
two other people.

00:52:04.910 --> 00:52:06.700
But I don't think there's any--

00:52:06.700 --> 00:52:08.920
there's no global,
universal solutions.

00:52:08.920 --> 00:52:10.790
There's just people.

